Citation.sAbstract: In this work, densities, F, refractive indices, nD, and dynamic viscosities, c, of the ternary mixtures of the  alcohols ethanol and 1-propanol + water with 1-ethyl-3-methylpyridinium ethylsulfate [empy][eSO4] have  been measured at T ) 298.15 K and atmospheric pressure. Excess molar volumes, VE, refractive index  deviations, AnD, and viscosity deviations, Ac, have been calculated from experimental data and fitted to  various correlation equations, obtaining good results. The excess properties have been used to test several  prediction models, finding out that symmetric models give lower deviations than asymmetric models.
Citation.sTitle: Experimental Determination, Correlation, and Prediction of Physical Properties of the Ternary Mixtures Ethanol and 1-Propanol + Water + 1-Ethyl-3-methylpyridinium Ethylsulfate at 298.15 K
